.TH "rivafb_cursor" 9 "rivafb_cursor" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rivafb_cursor \- hardware cursor function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rivafb_cursor
.BI "(struct fb_info *info "  ","
.BI "struct fb_cursor *cursor "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
pointer to info structure
.IP "cursor" 12
pointer to fbcursor structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A cursor function that supports displaying a cursor image via hardware.
Within the kernel, copy and invert rops are supported.  If exported
to user space, only the copy rop will be supported.

CALLED FROM
framebuffer hook
